{
  "number": 324,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/324",
  "title": "Only wrap the `autoHide` decorator when needed",
  "body": "Our current pattern in widgets that expose the `hideWhenNoResults` attribute is to wrap the React component inside an `autoHide` decorator, even if set to `false`. We then need to pass two new elements in the props: `hasResults` and `hideWhenNoResults`.\n\nI think this could be simplified by only wrapping with `autoHide` when the `hideWhenNoResults` attribute is set to `true` in the widget. We'll then only have to pass `hasResults` to the component. One less props to pass all the way down, will make things easier.\n\nI already tested that in a (now deleted) branch, this works well\n",
